cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SE, cs.DM

This paper discusses the use of Genetic Programming (GP) for machine learning tasks, specifically in binary classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the application of parsimony pressure to reduce the complexity of solutions, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper evaluates the results using statistical analysis, which could be classified under cs.DM (Data Mining).
